
@IBOutlet weak var someView: UIView!



1. install podfile
2. "import Vuukle"  add this line to your controller
3. create VuukleCommentsBuilder object in viewDidLoad method
4. need to call all required methods


firstVuukleTag ("firstTag") / secondVuukleTag ("secondTag")

TAG will be unique for each page where comment box opens.
TAG will be unique for each page where comment box opens.
For example:You are on the main app page with articles list -> you are choosing article -> it opens
and our library should have unique properties for each article like URL, TAGS, TITLE.
These properties You need to fill by yourself.
URL - will be article url from your domain/website to the article,
Tags - You need to paste tags separated by comma for each article(like you have on website/domain),
same for TITLE - title of the article on which library is now.



setVuukleApiKey()

Required field
Set your API key for API. To get API KEY you need :
1) Sign in to dashboard thouth vuukle.com
2) Navigate to domain from home page of dashboard (first page after signing in)
3) Choose in menu Integration, then API Docs from the dropdown
4) Then you will be able to see API and secret keys
---- or ----
1) Sign in to dashboard thouth vuukle.com
2) after signing in, in header you can find ‘Integration’ click -> choose API docs in the drop-down.


setVuukleArticleId("ARTICLE_ID")  -    get id from Vuukle site. Every article has unique id


setVuukleArticleTitle()
setVuukleUrl()


Required field
URL will be unique for each page where comment box opens.
For example:You are on the main app page with articles list -> you are choosing article -> it opens
and our library should have unique properties for each article like URL, TAGS, TITLE.
These properties You need to fill by yourself.
URL - will be article url from your domain/website to the article,
Tags - You need to paste tags separated by comma for each article(like you have on website/domain),
same for TITLE - title of the article on which library is now.


setVuukleEmoteVisible()  - set true for visible emote rating
setVuukleHost()

Required field
Set host for Api. Host - this is domain of the publisher’s site(e.g. indianexpress.com, thehindu.com etc.).
For example: You are the owner of indianexpress.com and have own app where want’s to setup this library,
so when library installed on your app, You should paste domain for ‘host’ property without http:// or https:// or www.


setVuukleSecretKey("SECRET_KEY")


Required field
Set your API key for API. To get SECRET KEY you need :
1) Sign in to dashboard through vuukle.com
2) Navigate to domain from home page of dashboard (first page after signing in)
3) Choose in menu Integration, then API Docs from the dropdown
4) Then you will be able to see api and SECRET keys
---- or ----
1) Sign in to dashboard thouth vuukle.com
2) after signing in, in header you can find ‘Integration’ click -> choose API docs in the drop-down.



setVuukleTimeZone()


Set time zone (for API)
@param timeZone get timezone from this resource
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_tz_database_time_zones


setAppName()  - set your application name

setArticleUrl() - set your article url

setAppID()  - set your application id

override func viewDidLoad() {

super.viewDidLoad()
var vuukle = VuukleCommentsBuilder()
vuukle.firstVuukleTag("articleTag1")
.secondVuukleTag("articleTag2")
.setVuukleApiKey("777854cd-9454-4e9f-8441-ef0ee894123e")
.setVuukleArticleId("00048")
.setVuukleArticleTitle("myArticleTitle")
.setVuukleBaseUrl("https://vuukle.com/api.asmx/")
.setVuukleEmoteVisible(true)
.setVuukleHost("vuukle.com")
.setVuukleSecretKey("07115720-6848-11e5-9bc9-002590f123ee")
.setVuukleTimeZone("Europe/Kiev")
.setVuukleUrl("http://mysite.com/article101")
.setVuukleTitle("Title")
.setAppName("myAppName")
.setArticleUrl("myArticleUrl")
.setAppID("myApId")
.buildVuukle(someView)
}